  "prompt": "What is the salary of a Scientific Officer in BARC?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the salary of a Scientific Officer at the Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC) in India typically ranges based on the pay scale and level of experience. Generally, a Scientific Officer can start at a pay scale around \u20b956,100 to \u20b91,77,500, depending on their qualifications (such as holding a Master's degree or a Ph.D.) and the specific position.\n\nIn addition to the basic pay, Scientific Officers at BARC may receive allowances such as house rent allowance (HRA), transport allowance, and other benefits, which can significantly affect the total compensation.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date salary information, I recommend checking the official BARC website or their latest job recruitment notices.",
